    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{t^{2}-t-6}{t-1}} \cdot {\frac{2t-2}{t+2}} =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>2\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right), t\ne -2\hbox{ and }t\ne 1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{t^{2}-t-6}{t-1}} \cdot {\frac{2t-2}{t+2}} 
      \amp = \frac{{\left(t+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}}{{t-1}} \cdot \frac{{2\mathopen{}\left(t-1\right)}}{{t+2}} \\
      \amp = {2\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right), t\ne -2\hbox{ and }t\ne 1}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>t+2</m> and <m>t - 1</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {-2, 1}</m>.</p>
</solution>
